(88, 14, 2, 'Japanese Market Information', '', '<p>Vietnam and Japan established formal diplomatic relations on September 21, 1973. So far, the two countries have built and constantly developing relations of friendship and cooperation is very close and comprehensive. Bilateral relations have reached a new peak, becoming &quot;strategic partnership for peace and prosperity in Asia&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src="http://dolab.gov.vn/Uploads/New/201372144133314.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>A. GENERAL INFORMATION</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. Geography:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Japan is an island nation in Northeast Asia. The Japanese islands are part of the underground mountain range stretching from Southeast Asia to Alaska. Japan has a coastline of 37,000 km, including 4 major islands in order from north to south are: Hokkaidō, Honshu, Shikoku, Kyushu and many small islands around. 73% hilly natural area nationwide, including many mountain is volcanic. Lanui highest mountain Fuji (Fujisan) 3776 meters high. Between the plateau and mountains is the basin. Japan has many waterfalls, streams, rivers and lakes. In particular, in Japan there are many hot springs, where millions of Japanese people usually go to rest and heal.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://dolab.gov.vn/Uploads/Uploads/New/201378144834844.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. Capital, the largest city</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Japan has 47 provinces and 12 cities, divided into nine regions, including Hokkaido, Tohoku, Kanto, Chubu, Kinki, Chugoku, Shikoku, Kyushu, and Okinawa. The capital is Tokyo - as well as the center of politics, economics and Japanese information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://dolab.gov.vn/Uploads/Uploads/New/201378145032899.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. The area, population, population structure, employment rate and unemployment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3.1. Acreage:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Japan has an area of ​​about 377 829 km&sup2;, is a small country, from north to south length of about 3.500km, hilly terrain due to Japan only very little land available for cultivation. The cultivated fields accounted for 12.3%, fruit growing area of ​​1.1% and accounting for 0.2% grass land area of ​​the country. In contrast, forest land accounts for the largest proportion, 66.5% of the total land area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3.2. Population:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2012, Japan has around 127.37 million, accounting for about 1.81% of the world population and ranks 10th among the most populous country. Japan&#39;s population is unevenly distributed, mostly concentrated in major centers: Tokyo, Yokohama, Nagoya, Osaka, Kobe and Kyoto. Tokyo with 12.7 million people and a population density of about 54,700 Highest people / km&sup2;, while in Hokkaido - the most densely populated province has density 74 people / km&sup2;. The population in cities and towns accounted for about 4/5 of Japan&#39;s population, only about 1/5 of the remaining population lives in the coastal plains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Japan&#39;s population is aging so fast, low birth rates lead to domestic labor force is shrinking, lack of manpower in severe working age.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3.3. The unemployment rate in Japan</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Japan&#39;s Ministry of Labor has announced that the unemployment rate in this country in May 5/2012 fell 4.4%, 0.2% lower compared to May 4. Accordingly, the number of unemployed in May / 2012 nearly 3 million people, accounting for 3.3% of Japan&#39;s labor force; the number of employed people increased by almost 63 million people, ie every 100 jobseekers, the 81 people get jobs, mainly in the construction sector in the Northeast.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The unemployment rate fell to prove the 3rd largest economy in the world is recovering from the earthquake led to tsunami 3/2011 month.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Climate and weather:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Japanese climate changed markedly under 4 Spring - Lower - Thu - East. Spring to early March is marked by cold air. In late April and May, Japan&#39;s plains have nice weather most of the year, the average temperature of 120C in Sapporo, Tokyo and 19,20C 18,40C in Osaka. Last spring, the temperature and humidity rise, and it is identified by broad, thick clouds about 300-400 km block the sun and makes the weather less stuffy. Intermittent rain but can be very loud.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Summer rain often from the south and west of Japan in early June and progress to the north at the end of the month. Between the hot summer and muggy night stand by the wind. The average temperature in August in Tokyo is 26,70C and 280C in Osaka. Last August warm monsoon, repeated early summer rains, in Sapporo, Sendai and Tokyo have much rain in September (rain Shurin).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In autumn, a season of rain Shurin late fall short transition in the early to mid-October, depending on latitude and lasts until November, at the start of winter. Fall weather is cool and pleasant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Winter came to Japan from January 12 to January 2. Most Japanese regions with snow in winter. Northeast monsoon blowing from the Asian continent to the system is blocked by hills along Japan caused heavy snow to central Honshu from Hokkaido. Niigata province is one of the provinces with the most snow in the world with 8 meters thick snow record. Average monthly temperature in winter in Asahikawa city is -8,50C and holds the record lowest temperature in Japan -410C.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5. Language</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Japan, there are 12 languages ​​belonging to the Japanese language, a language not native Japanese language group is known Ainu and several foreign languages, including English, Chinese is used by Japanese.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>6. Religion</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Japan there are two main religions are Shinto (Shinto) and Buddhism. Shinto has no founder, no separate types of scriptures such as the Bible or the Buddhist scriptures. Buddhism began in India from the 6th century BC. A major branch of Buddhism, Mahayana branch or called Mahayana Buddhism was introduced to Japan. Buddhism was introduced to Japan from China and Korea in the 6th century<strong>.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>7. The currency, VND exchange rate [DTD1]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yen is the currency of Japan, which is &yen; symbols, and code is JPY, issued by the Bank of Japan released.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Exchange rates: 1 Yen &asymp; 257 VND (according to the time of 21/06/2011)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://dolab.gov.vn/Uploads/Uploads/New/201378145052501.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>8. Traffic, transportation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Japan, the public transport commuter trains mainly. Japan&#39;s transport system is highly developed, in large cities, just walk 5 ~ 15 minutes to reach the nearest station. Besides, in some suburbs and rural areas, the Japanese use the bus (without a car). The city will have a bus if the train is not convenient.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>B. INFORMATION ON LABOR MIGRATION</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>I. Japan&#39;s labor market</p>\r\n\r\n<p>* Selection Criteria:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Aged 18 years and older; meet the requirements of health</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Education: High school and older</p>\r\n\r\n<p>* Industry: trainee and internship in textile mills, engineering, plastics, seafood processing, carpentry, construction, agriculture ...</p>\r\n\r\n<p>* Contract duration: maximum of 3 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>* Average income: between 80,000 yen - 100,000 yen / month (equivalent to VND 22,000,000 - 28,000,000 VND / month</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>II. Situation Vietnam intern training in Japan</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vietnam and Japan established formal diplomatic relations on September 21, 1973. So far, the two countries have built and constantly developing relations of friendship and cooperation is very close and comprehensive. Bilateral relations have reached a new peak, becoming &quot;strategic partnership for peace and prosperity in Asia&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Japan is the country with the third largest economy globally. Demand for foreign workers to receive Japan&#39;s huge, annually receives over 100,000 foreign trainees, of which about 6,000 trainees Vietnam. Japan is considered a huge potential market for Vietnam trainee. Currently, Vietnam has nearly 20,000 trainees are working in Japan in 63 different industry groups, is the country with the number of trainees the second largest of the 15 countries sending, just behind China , ahead of Indonesia, Philippines and Thailand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overall, the trainee Vietnam are suitable jobs, good working conditions and a stable income.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://dolab.gov.vn/Uploads/Uploads/New/20137815236508.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>III. The cooperation program included trainees from Vietnam to Japan</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. Cooperation Program Cooperation with international trainees in Japan (JITCO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vietnam officially trainee professional training in Japan since 1992 within the framework of the memorandum on &quot;The sending and receiving foreign trainees to study in Japan&quot; by the Ministry of Labour - war Invalids and Social Affairs Cooperation Organization signed with Japan international industrial Training (JITCO). Through this program, Japan provides vocational training to help young people improve skills Vietnam, access to advanced techniques and modern technology in order to return home while contributing actively to the development developed country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So far, more than 120 enterprises Vietnam sending prestige, eligibility approved by JITCO trainees taken professional training in Japan. Currently, Vietnam trainees are being trained in Japan in areas such as electronics, mechanical processing, garment industry, seafood processing, construction, agriculture, shipbuilding ... in most provinces Japanese but mainly concentrated in the region of Gifu, Konto, Kansai, Aichi, Hiroshima ...</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to statistics of the Organization JITCO, trainee quantity Vietnam to practice in Japan is increasing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. The program of cooperation with the Agency for Human Resources Development in Japan (JAPAN IM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the field of sending trainees, besides partnerships with JITCO, from the end of 2005, the Ministry of Labour - Invalids and Social Affairs signed an agreement with the Agency for Human Resources Development International Japan ( JAPAN IM). Intern training in Japan under this program barely pay the costs before the exit, except for health care expenses and fees, passport and visa, accommodation expenses, in training time before sending. After completion of the training period and practice techniques on water, held IM JAPAN will support each trainee sum 600,000 yen (about $ 7,500) to support the integration and find a new job or self create jobs for themselves. For trainees who wish to work in Japanese companies in Vietnam, organized in collaboration with IM Japan will Ministry of Labour - Invalids and Social Affairs to contact the company to support employment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This program is consistent with the spirit of the Decision No. 71/2009 / QD-TTg of the Prime Minister to support workers in the poorest districts, remote areas to work abroad. The agency directly implement this program in Vietnam that foreign labor centers (Ministry of Labor - Invalids and Social Affairs).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. A number of other programs:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Besides the cooperation given trainee and practicing skills for professional training and technical internship in Japan, Vietnam has also provided technical workers skilled, information technology engineers, who have a university degree and postgraduate degree in the field for Japan. Currently, the working time of the engineers, experts in Vietnam in Japan is three years and can be extended for another two years, the average monthly salary of about 250,000 yen / month (about $ 3,000), is to provide housing , electricity, water and living amenities such as gas stove, refrigerator, furnace ... high income level and environment, advanced working conditions in Japan are attractive factors for new engineers. However, compared to the trainee program, hiring engineers and experts also more difficult, require a longer training in Japanese but many times higher efficiency, labor quality is guaranteed and rarely arise In working process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition, since 2012, within the framework of the Economic Partnership Agreement Vietnam - Japan (VJEPA), the two parties agreed to implement the Program applicants nursing, nurses to work in Japan. Ministry of Labour - Invalids and Social Affairs is the Prime Minister is the focal point for the implementation of this program. Vietnam is the third country, after the Philippines and Indonesia, the official cooperation agreement put candidates nursing and nurses to work and study in Japan - the country the world&#39;s leading developer of medical services . This is a great opportunity for the nurses, orderlies Vietnam will be trained in a professional working environment, raise the level of their own while working in Japan as well as be able to use the knowledge, learning useful experience when returning to work in the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>IV. Some provisions of the Immigration Management Act relating to receiving trainees:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. Resident status:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Immigration Administration Law of Japan provided for foreigners entering Japan would like to declare the application file status. Depending on the condition, status and purpose of entry, authorities consider immigration to grant resident status. After acquiring the status, foreigners who wish to enter Japan will diplomatic missions of Japan in the host country to apply for entry visa. Upon arriving in Japan, foreigners are only allowed to conduct operations in accordance with the purposes stipulated in resident status granted by the Japanese side.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For trainee status is &quot;Intern skills&quot;. Thus, trainees are only allowed to carry out the activities of a trainee skills. In cases where trainees dropped out of practice to go to work in restaurants or other plant ... will be in violation of provisions on residence status and will be deported from Japan. Residence status of trainees will be recorded on the visa and passport holders of each trainee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. Duration of stay:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Content visa pasted into your passport trainee will show include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Resident status;<br />\r\nStorage time;<br />\r\nDay allowed entry;<br />\r\nAirport name (local) where entry gate;<br />\r\nThe residence time is the time trainees will be allowed to stay in Japan to conduct activities to practice skills. Usually the Japanese Ministry of Justice, which is directly managed agencies Immigration will grant resident status for a period of 6 months or 1 year for trainees. Stay expired, the receiving agency should carry out the procedures for the renewal status of residence for a total period of stay not exceeding 3 years for skilled trainees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. Change the status:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Under the provisions of the Immigration Administration Law, foreigners with resident status want to change the purpose of the procedures for applying to the Minister of Justice (represented by the director of the Department of Immigration local ) to change the status of residence for the purpose in accordance with the</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Extension of duration of stay:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Extension of duration of stay is the procedure when a foreign nguwofi in Japan wants to continue the activities that the current status of their permit, but stays prepared expired.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5. Entry to Japan while resident status:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to regulations, foreigners staying in Japan is free to leave at any time Japan without through any special procedures. However, when out of Japan, status of residence and duration of stay in Japan from which it will take effect. To go back to Japan, foreigners will have to do the procedures to apply new visa procedures more complicated and time consuming. Japanese Immigration Law allows foreigners are longer length of stay in Japan is re-scene procedures before leaving Japan that person. Those who have completed national procedures for re-entry will be exempt from visa upon entry to Japan and only do the testing procedures of entry alone.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>V. Instructions on visas for Vietnam</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To get entry to Japan to work or practice skills, Vietnam workers must labor visa, as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Where in Japan more than 90 days, or jobs with lucrative purposes, the proposal must first apply for a certificate of eligibility to stay in Japan at the Immigration Bureau Ministry of Justice Japan Local places near best (telephone number and entry administration of the Ministry of justice Japan: 03-3580-4111).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(1) Passport</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(2) A declaration applying for Visa (01 sheets)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(3) 01 pictures 4,5cm x 4,5cm</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(4) the certificate of eligibility to stay in Japan</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(5) Documents verifying accuracy itself (01)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ In case of technical labors, skills: The labor contracts, recruitment notice ...</p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ Where to go for professional training: Legal receiving trainees ...</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to the foregoing documents, as the case may Embassy or State Department will require the production of any other papers. Please note, the case does not produce the requested documents may not be receiving dossiers Visa or Visa slow.</p>\r\n', '21/06/2016 20:13:15', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/lJFkRZaQuR7bO5xLqlpGQhQeHlfaCJDAwbthNb3G_dfijm-i3qEpl8sIt8DNV4MUoyXRuupI0fwTKcr3JNKkZjILluxq5NoQtBlMpo2qs1CFVN8OksMi1W9ifEtPCZ6hMhR5OCz2JROhVdxORJTXR1uDL75zGnODRr9gMDxwjn1ThdFHM2D7mPtMpPz3kmckN3x23iS6MbLvhA0TBw-zzdh448THqt1Iy96u7HHqcNGkyL8UM1o8e9JgFsx-l_8GQwp42N2AfTRDVT7kKfWan7NgB1NHChCUL47-FznAMzERQZ-qpMeGCJ2-YNrBEigmgWsDUcTSJJfXFfT4bK-gNPIXaF5X9iXzBihbgVGiPTeHseXDDlKbj0zZJY7kZo2VNLIIZCUVh7LXGcmLypSN04ytme1-PIJHgCP4yypDcTvs7umEJhNti41T1yq_mmOIAGqQoMUh7W6INTDLxKySd3HV8nzFM5uXqPDCwB8QBVs3cDYeYuJmrcweVJT5UGU1BQHNZQ1iZTptngxZff9e-V5P36DnhtMeUCym1SVnE0chUwJbD19IZD_2N591ultETUYMXTW0Ti2mpvWQkkTKDeuhseoxCD8=w968-h623-no', 0, 'Japanese-market-information'),
(89, 14, 2, 'Taiwan market information', '', '<p><strong><em>I. An overview of Taiwan General</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Tri Geography 1.1.Vi</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Taiwan is the name of an island and an archipelago in East Asia, including the island of Taiwan and some smaller surrounding islands such as Penghu Islands, Finland self, Green Island, and the State of Ryukyu. The main island, close to the southeast coast of mainland China Taiwan Strait is about 180 kilometers (112 mi) and is separated from the Fujian province of China. Islands form part of the territory of the Republic of China (also known as Taiwan), after this administration to take the Chinese mainland in the Chinese Civil War. Taiwan East China Sea lies to the north, is located east of the Philippine Sea, Luzon Strait lies directly to the south and the South China Sea is located in the southwest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Taiwan has 35 883 km2 area (13,855 sq mi). The island has a contrast, two-thirds of the territory in the east mainly mountainous region located in the mountains running from the north to the southern tip of the island, while the west is from the flat plains to gentle waves - home to most of Taiwan&#39;s population. Taiwan&#39;s highest peaks with altitudes Ngoc Son is 3,952 meters (12,966 ft), and there are five other peaks over 3,500 meters high. This has led to the island of Taiwan became the world&#39;s fourth tallest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><sup><img alt="" src="http://dolab.gov.vn/Uploads/Uploads/New/201378171840913.png" /></sup></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Much of the east of Taiwan is mountainous, with plains with gentle slopes on the west. Penghu archipelago is located west of the island of Taiwan (photos from satellites)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>1.2.Khi Hau</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The climate on the island is generally tropical ocean and many seasonal changes in the north and the mountains. Climate has 4 seasons, spring from March to April, summer from May to September, the fall from October to November, winter from December to February 2. The annual average temperature ranges from 25 degrees C to 28 degrees C. Northern Taiwan usually rain from late October to may 3. Southern hotter northern climate, summer southwest monsoon usually accompanied by rain. In the month of 7.8 and 9 in Taiwan often stormy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>1.3.Thu capital and major cities in Taiwan</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>1.3.1. Taipei (Taipei) </em></strong>is a major city located in northern Taiwan and is also the capital of this country. Apart from the main island of Taiwan, Taipei also include Penghu Islands and surrounding islets. Not only is the capital, the center of political, administrative, cultural, Taipei is also the region with developed economy most powerful, concentrated industrial zones of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="http://dolab.gov.vn/Uploads/Uploads/New/2013781719234.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to the capital&#39;s administrative center, economy, politics and culture of Taiwan, a number of major cities are also on the rise, contributing to the overall development of the economy flourishes Taiwan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1.3.2. Taichung</strong> has the same meaning as the name &quot;Taipei&quot;, Taichung (Taichung) is a city in west central Taiwan. Taichung has an area of ​​about 163 km2, is the third largest city of Taiwan, after Taipei and Kaohsiung. This city is considered the cultural center of the country&#39;s education with many temples, ruins. In cities with more than 10 parishes and pastoral centers both for the people of migrant workers from the Philippines. Taichung is considered a very romantic city on the natural scenery, climate and abundance of culture, cuisine, shopping.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="http://dolab.gov.vn/Uploads/Uploads/New/201378171917458.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1.3.3. Tainan: </strong>Taiwan is divided into three main areas: Taipei, Taichung, and Tainan (Tainan) - a city located in the southern region of Taiwan. Tainan is the fourth largest city of Taiwan, but it is the city with the oldest history. It served as the capital of Taiwan during the long years of being dominated. Contrary to Taipei, Tainan no more bustling industrial or commercial development of strong, but this place is known for its rich agricultural background, diversity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="http://dolab.gov.vn/Uploads/Uploads/New/201378171930616.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1.3.4. Kaohsiung (Kaohsiung) </strong>is the second largest city of Taiwan, after the capital, Taipei. However, compared to Taipei, the street traffic more smoothly spacious and systems MRT subway and operated since 2008. located in southern Kaohsiung Taiwan, is the center of manufacturing, filtration the largest oil and transport there. Kaohsiung Harbor is one of the four largest ports in the world, the majority of oil were imported into Taiwan from the port area. Besides, Kaohsiung City was the center of the shipbuilding industry and the key naval base.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="http://dolab.gov.vn/Uploads/Uploads/New/201378171940162.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>1.4.Dan number, language, religion, customs and culture:</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Population:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Taiwan&#39;s population as of 2012 to approximately 25 million people (excluding Kinmen and Matsu), most of which reside in the island of Taiwan. Approximately 98% are Han Chinese. Approximately 2% of the population of Taiwan, about 458,000 people were listed as the Taiwanese aborigines. Taipei is home to the highest population density, followed by Kaohsiung, about 59% of Taiwan&#39;s population is concentrated in four major cities of Taipei, Taichung, Kaohsiung and Tainan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Population growth rate: 0.61% (2006 estimate); 0.81% (2000 estimate)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Age structure: 0-14 years: 19.4% (male 2,330,951 / female 2,140,965); 15-64 years: 70.8% (male 8,269,421 / female 8,040,169); 65 years and over: 9.8% (male 1,123,429 / female 1,131,152) (2006 estimate). Age structure of the population of Taiwan has an aging trend.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- The labor force: 10.6 million (in 2005)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Employment by Sector: Services 58.2%, 35.8% industry, agriculture 6% (in 2005)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- The rate of unemployment: 4:28% (as of 9/2011.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Economic Taiwan&#39;s economy is capitalist, export growth was a key driver for the industrialization, the demand for labor increases. Besides, due to the age structure of the population of Taiwan has rapidly aging trend in recent years Taiwan should soon implement policies that care for the elderly and children is quite comprehensive, which work hard care of the elderly, children become a popular profession in Taiwan, accompanied by the demand for labor in this sector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>1.5.Ngon Language:</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Mandarin standard (also known as Mandarin) is recognized as an official language of Taiwan, this language is the majority people use, is mainly teaching language in schools. Mandarin is the main language of instruction in schools. A large part of the population can speak Taiwanese. Aboriginal groups, most speak their native languages, the indigenous languages ​​do not belong to Chinese or Sino-Tibetan language which belongs to the Austronesian languages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- In addition, English is also becoming quite popular in Taiwan. English quite enshrined in Taiwan schools.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Writing the traditional form of Chinese characters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>1.6.Ton teachers:</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The majority of Taiwan&#39;s population of religious people, they mostly follow Mahayana Buddhism and Taoism. Many others follow folk religion. Confucianism and Confucian culture has a great influence on the spiritual life, especially in the common conception of ethics and morality. According to the CIA World Factbook, the 80% to 93% of the population with a mixture of Buddhism, Taoism and Confucianism.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Christianity in Taiwan mainly Protestant believers or Episcopal short. Taiwanese aborigines to Christianity, with 64% of this religion, the church is a highlight that their villages be different with the villages of Fujian and Hakka.<br />\r\n<strong>Religion in Taiwan (Due to the Taiwan authorities provided</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table align="center" border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:583px">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>T&ocirc;n gi&aacute;o</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Tỉ lệ</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><a href="http://vi.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ph%E1%BA%ADt_gi%C3%A1o" title="Phật">Phật gi&aacute;o</a></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>35.1%</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><a href="http://vi.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C4%90%E1%BA%A1o_gi%C3%A1o" title="Đạo">Đạo gi&aacute;o</a></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>33%</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><a href="http://vi.wikipedia.org/wiki/V%C3%B4_th%E1%BA%A7n" title="Vô">V&ocirc; thần</a></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>14%</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><a href="http://vi.wikipedia.org/wiki/C%C6%A1_%C4%90%E1%BB%91c_gi%C3%A1o" title="Cơ">Cơ Đốc gi&aacute;o</a></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>3.9%</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><a href="http://vi.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=I-Kuan_Tao&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" title="I-Kuan">I-Kuan Tao</a></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>3.5%</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="http://dolab.gov.vn/Uploads/Uploads/New/20137817201523.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1.7.Dong money:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The official currency of Taiwan is NT or NT (NT $), including banknotes and coins.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Banknotes with face value of NT $ 50 yuan, 100 yuan, 500 yuan, 1,000 yuan, 2,000 yuan and.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Coins with denominations of NT $ 1, 5. 10, 20, 50 yuan and 5 jiao.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Currently, the exchange rate between the Taiwan dollar and Vietnam dong: 1NT $ = 715.90 VND<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="http://dolab.gov.vn/Uploads/Uploads/New/201378172016469.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>8.He transport and communications:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- The transport system is well developed in Taiwan, convenient travel. International airport in Taoyuan Province and Kaohsiung, in addition to the domestic airport. North-South highway and road system, the complete railway, linking the areas together. In the city there are buses system development. In the city of Taipei and Kaohsiung metro system modernization. Everyone compliance with traffic rules, regulations phanduong right, sitting on a motorcycle must wear a helmet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Network communication is also Taiwan&#39;s development, and telephone number of the highest in the world, so the contact by phone, fax, email, both domestically and outside Taiwan&#39;s quite easy convenient. You can call in the &quot;boots&quot; public phone on the street by purchasing calling cards by buying phone cards in stores across Taiwan ELEVEN there, here also have fax service and a number of other services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>II. Information on migrant workers</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>►Tinh formation of migrant workers:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Loan station is relatively developed regions so in the manual labor industries, heavy, locals do not go unheard, mainly to foreign workers as laborers Vietnam, Thailand, Indonesia , Philippines. Taiwan Water itself does not export labor to other countries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>-Type Of trades in Taiwan mainly factory workers, employees of nursing homes and assisting the family and fishing industries offshore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>►Nhung key features of the immigration laws, visa regulations:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A. Please work visas:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vietnamese citizens want to go the full 20 years of age with a term workers in Taiwan to adopt a labor broker in Vietnam. Labor brokers Vietnam must have labor export license by the Government of Vietnam and Labor Committee Taiwan Institute of Public Administration confirmed. Visa records are full of labor need originals and copies of the documents as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Vietnam passport with expiry date of at least 6 months according to international practices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Form the labor visa declaration, this declaration by the Office form we provide for free. Each employee should carefully read the rules are printed on the back of each sheet form and personally sign the declaration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Two 4x6 photos taken within the last 6 months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Licence recruited by the Commission for Labor Administration Taiwan Institute grant (the license code 002; 007; 016).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Entry Permit labor committee of the Taiwan Institute of Public Administration level (enclosed license codes recruited 016).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Form dossier evaluation Vietnam employer to work for a limited time in Taiwan by the Office of Economics and Culture of Vietnam in Taipei levels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. Mail the request of the employer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Power of attorney by the employer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. The labor contract was signed between the employee and employer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10. Certificate of enough health workers abroad by one of Bach Mai Hospital, Saint Paul, Transport I, Hue Central Hospital, Cho Ray Hospital, Thong Nhat and only take effect 3 months from the date of grant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>11. vocational apprenticeship certificate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>12. judicial record is valid for 6 months from date of issuance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>13. The commitment to salary and other costs of foreign workers to work in Taiwan with the signature of the employee, the signature and seal of the director of Vietnam brokers and agencies state management of Vietnam brokers there.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>14. The lending commitments if the loan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>15. Invoices detailed charges of brokers Vietnam for workers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>B. Immigration Law, residing in Taiwan:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If using a visa for entry, within 15 days after entry procedures are required to apply for a residence permit:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>►Nhung key features of the labor law, work permits:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Some key features of the labor laws in Taiwan:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ The labor contract is 3 years. Maximum workers can work in Taiwan is 12 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ Basic salary: 18 780 yuan / month on labor 8am (equivalent 14,000,000 VND). Basic salary hourly increased NT $ 103.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ In terms of employment insurance payment: The amount of labor insurance payable / month = [NT $ 18,780 (salary insurance) x 7.5% (insurance premiums ratio) x 20% (share of people paid labor)] = NT $ 282 / month.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ On the withholding of personal income tax for foreign workers:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>a) For foreign workers who reside in Taiwan less than 183 days in a tax year (from 01/01 to 31/12):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Where the income each month from 1.5 times basic salary, ie from 28 170 NT $ / month or more, the deduction of 18% of total income. The calculation formula is as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Taxes payable / month = monthly income x 18%</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Where the monthly income under 1.5 times the basic salary, which is less than NT $ 28,170 / month, deduct 6% of total income. The calculation formula is as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Taxes payable / month = monthly income by 6%</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>b) For foreign workers who reside in Taiwan full 183 days or more a tax year, the deduction of 5% of taxable income. The calculation formula is as follows:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>[Taxes payable / year = (total income / year - tax-free allowance - the standard deduction - the deductions) x 5%]</p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ On the issue of food, the Commission specified labor countries sending laborers to work in Taiwan obtained the prescribed level of 0 to NT $ 2,500 / month.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ Foreign employees and losing touch quit continuously for 3 days or terminate the employment relationship, the employer within 3 days must inform in writing the agency and local police agencies .</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Labor permit: Within 15 days after entry workers and roots used to labor to Taiwan Commission permits employers. When the work permit expired nearly, if the employer agrees to continue to employ them, the employer must apply for a license extension of labor hire workers with the Commission within 60 days before the permit employers expiring old</p>\r\n', '21/06/2016 20:26:30', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/xyDpY1phMRZZNu5dmc7Lm-AK9Xfc5LpbRXd55XQQdkHkjPi31mD5FOQqX3he5ekjuXMpFlahUvLxbARDMewT4naOnEfsu8kEGFwKzE29zujsLPz1lN5I7G6LoURh-Wh-Qxm0vw_FtzaWg5WTxYy9ymSGaPxPcKk2m2qFJFolIaew8rDU0dZu1rpg9l_PRw0p4nG-gVaZJSWzA_ULlGBgd9LYRxwtH2KFfF3776lvmSA6dgkWKwtnIZ_dO05_u1fHMeKWqAqHqfOsqcMAT8cQOkEKll8sEUx7OiFsExl9D2oYhaJ2vcs3ZIHosScPtUJb21shmJDCltEA5QEZDrE-GSukvis1wAkkkyMjsbxm7JwlVgm3lSQrq-TwQNboVYBK6a10wdpnxdxb7E19uKfPG9WSQPTmITozjH2IxeN5M0DXiDgNvSH6s_4WuWAdIFNMFF5xU2I_YUxpOPbv4dBT0B2sxjAqtlvKK_3E3DJ_AFhXc9K9CEd_KaCkMjzv37CC1GyllLAdkiKh_KczsqRnzd7DQ6zMnF2cN5h_KSkwdCRyup0gBSDvwP4F48928N7ujmreylKnWnmHOyMZUGkcCPGN71NUzsU=w1068-h667-no', 0, 'taiwan-market-information'),
